#fill nan value
#mode() fill nan for categorical data [0] is always better to chose eg. [1,2,1,2,3,5,1,2,1,2] mode[0] always give first num
data['University Rating']=data['University Rating'].fillna(data['University Rating'].mode()[0])
data['GRE Score']=data['GRE Score'].fillna(data['GRE Score'].mean())
data['TOEFL Score']=data['TOEFL Score'].fillna(data['TOEFL Score'].mean())

Regularization in regression means is our model is over fitting means ,test question given from train question paper ,it means paper is leaked os accuracy is more that is called regularization. it is 2 type. 1.LASSO, Lasso is very harsh it remove coeffecinet which have less weightage 2.RIDGE,Ridge consider less weightage which have less contributaion in regression
